.TH VITTE-LINKER 1 "March 2026" "vitte 03.2025" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vitte-linker \- linker entrypoint for Vitte toolchain compatibility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vitte-linker
[\fIoptions\fR] \fI<input>\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vitte-linker
is installed for compatibility with legacy tooling.
Depending on installation payload, it can resolve to:
.IP \(bu 2
a dedicated linker binary, or
.IP \(bu 2
the main
.BR vitte (1)
driver fallback.
.P
Use
.B vitte
for the canonical end-user workflow.
When routed through compatibility symlinks/wrappers, startup logs include
\fB[compat] vitte-linker mode via vitte X.Y.Z\fR to avoid wrapper confusion.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, non-zero on linking/driver errors.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
See
.BR vitte (1)
for linker-related environment variables and runtime paths.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
vitte-linker --help
vitte-linker build/main.vit
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vitte (1),
.BR vittec (1),
.BR vitte-editor (1)
